childElements.name: TextBlock7
childElements.propertySetConfig:
{ "controlWidth" : 12, "label" : "TextBlock7", "text" : "

Underground piping associated with aboveground oil storage tanks is regulated by the State Department of Environmental Protection (DEP) (207) 287-7688. Underground piping must be installed by a DEP Certified Installer. All underground piping associated with motor fuel tanks must be registered with the DEP. A permit is not required for a tank that is part of a listed generator unit. The unit must be installed according to the manufacturer’s requirements. The capacity of a generator tank is counted for purposes of a Spill Prevention Control and Countermeasures Plan (SPCC).

", "show" : null, "dataJSON" : false, "HTMLTemplateId" : "", "textKey" : "", "sanitize" : false }
